A '''corbelled tomb''' is a generic term given to burial [[tomb]]s with [[corbel]]led roofs rather than simple slabs, which generally denote an earlier type of construction.

In Europe they include the [[Mycenaean period|Mycenean]] [[Beehive tombs|tholos]] tomb type.

