The '''Graduate School of Business Administration Zurich (GSBA Zurich)'''<ref>{{cite journal|title=Graduate School of Business Administration Zurich |url=http://www.b-school-net.de/MBA_Program_Profiles/mba_profiles_2003/gsba_2003.htm |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140717230603/http://www.b-school-net.de/MBA_Program_Profiles/mba_profiles_2003/gsba_2003.htm |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2014-07-17 |journal=http://www.b-school-net.de }}</ref> is the oldest and largest business school in German-speaking Europe.<ref>{{cite journal |title=An interview with Albert Stähli|url=http://www.accessmba.com/?id=258|journal=http://www.accessmba.com}}</ref>

The school was founded in 1968 as "Oekreal Management Zentrum" offering Swiss professional degrees.<ref>{{cite journal |title=The GSBA Zurich Success Story|url=http://www.mba4success.com/pages/news/news_content.php?id=62|journal=http://www.mba4success.com}}</ref>

It was an international Business School (accredited by EDUQUA) at lakeside [[Zurich, Switzerland]]. In July 2009 [[Peter Lorange]],<ref>{{cite journal |title=Peter Lorange|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/peter-lorange/|journal=https://www.forbes.com}}</ref> former IMD president, bought GSBA Zurich.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Peter Lorange: What does the former head of IMD want with his new school?|url=http://www.mba-channel.com/channel/article/peter-lorange-what-does-the-former-head-of-imd-want-with-his-new-school/|journal=http://www.mba-channel.com|date = 10/01/2010}}</ref>

==Academic programs==
GSBA offers master of Science Programs in Marketing, HRM, Finance, MIS/IT, OM/Logistics, two Bachelor Programs like BBA and BSC as well as an international PhD Program. All of those programs are part-time for working executives.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Lorange Institute of Business Zurich|url=http://www.topmba.com/institution/lorange-institute-business-zurich|journal=http://www.topmba.com}}</ref>

The school also offers a World Executive MBA being the first academic alliance in Business administration offering management modules in fundamental disciplines of business administration on five continents in Brazil, South Africa, India, Russia and Switzerland.<ref>{{cite journal |title=World Executive MBA @ GSBA Zurich|url=http://letsgmat.blogspot.be/2010/05/world-executive-mba-gsba-zurich.html|journal=http://letsgmat.blogspot.be|date = 26 May 2010}}</ref>

